==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deaconess
<hw>Dea"con*ess</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>
<def>A female deacon</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Primitive Ch.)</fld>
<def>One of an order of women whose duties resembled those of
deacons.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Ch. of Eng. and Prot. Epis. Ch.)</fld>
<def>A woman set apart for church work by a bishop.</def> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>A woman chosen as a helper in church work, as among the
Congregationalists.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deaconhood</ent>⟦br⟧
